.wp_slug phone-synchronisation-syncevolution
[syncEvolution][] is fully-featured implementation of the [SyncML][] protocol. Despite it's name, syncEvolution supports *any* SyncML based client or server -- [Evolution][] being only one example -- with many [choices][compatibility] available. I use [Thunderbird][] as my main email, calendering and contact manager (aka [Personal Information Manager][PIM]) and with a bit of work, syncEvolution will run nicely with it.

Version 1.0 brings about two interesting features: direct synchronisation over bluetooth and a built-in, personal SyncML server.

Usecase 1: backup phone data to computer
----------------------------------------

All modern mobiles implement the SyncML protocol to some degree. Correspondingly, vendors release an application to go with it. However, in my experience, these are Windows only, proprietary, bloated pieces of junk.

